item.title: Making Sense of America’s Credit Card Debt
item.description: Credit card debt is at an all-time high in America. Half of all Americans with a credit card have carried a balance in the last year, and one in three Americans have more credit card debt than emergency savings. Plus, the cost of this debt is increasing, with high interest rates becoming the norm. It can be easy to view credit card debt as a personal failure, a result of overspending on non-essentials, and while that’s true in a lot of cases, nearly a third of credit card holders in the U.S...
